#Text=Dismantle a Computer
#Text=This is a step-by-step guide for people to follow when completely taking a computer apart .
#Text=Steps
#Text=You are going to start off by removing the side panels on the computer case .
#Text=These panels are often secured by a few screws on the back of the case .
#Text=Unscrew the screws then slide the side panels off .
#Text=After the panels are off , you will see the motherboard .
#Text=There will be multiple cables coming off of the motherboard that run back to the power supply , hard drive(s) , fan(s) , and possibly more depending on the computer .
#Text=Go ahead and unplug all of these cables from the motherboard .
#Text=After you unplug all of the cables that are attached to the motherboard , go ahead and unplug any cables that attached to the drives towards the front of the computer .
#Text=Now that all of the power supply cables are unplugged , you can now remove the power supply .
#Text=On the back of the case , there will be at least four screws holding the power supply in place .
#Text=Go ahead and start unscrewing those screws .
#Text=If the power supply is mounted in the top section of the case , be sure to hold it as you are unscrewing so that it does not drop !
#Text=After the power supply is removed , look to see if there is anything plugged into the motherboard 's PCI slot(s) .
#Text=If so go ahead unscrew the screw holding the card in place .
#Text=Once you do that , you can push the tab in on the PCI slot to remove the card .
#Text=After the PCI card(s) is removed , you can now take the motherboard out of the case .
#Text=The motherboard is screwed onto the multiple case stand-offs .
#Text=Go ahead and unscrew all of these screws .
#Text=( It is recommended to lay the computer on its side for this step . )
#Text=After you remove the motherboard , go ahead and remove all of the drives from the drive cage at the front of the computer case .
#Text=These drives are going to be held in tray that will just slide straight out of the drive cage .
#Text=If you wish , you can remove the drives from the tray by unscrewing the four screws that secure the drives to the tray .
#Text=At this point , all components should be removed from the computer case .
#Text=The only thing remaining is the RAM and the CPU still attached to the motherboard .
#Text=To remove the RAM , just push on the tabs found on the end of the sticks and it will just pop out .
#Text=The last thing to do is to remove the CPU from the motherboard .
#Text=The CPU is under the CPU cooler .
#Text=In order to remove the CPU cooler , pull up on the four tabs around the fan and it should just pop off .
#Text=The CPU will just lift out of its socket and then all the components to the computer will be disassembled .
